The `array_unique()` function works by maintaining an internal array of keys (or indices) that have already been encountered. When it encounters an element for the first time, it adds its index to the internal array. When it encounters an element that exists in the internal array, it skips that element. The final output is a new array with all the elements present in the input array that are not duplicated.

